(238, '_transient_a1a994fe14eed12a6d93ddc6b4df76aa', 'O:8:\"stdClass\":25:{s:4:\"name\";s:21:\"WordPress Beta Tester\";s:4:\"slug\";s:21:\"wordpress-beta-tester\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"2.0.4\";s:6:\"author\";s:66:\"<a href=\"https://blog.ftwr.co.uk/\">Peter Westwood, Andy Fragen</a>\";s:14:\"author_profile\";s:36:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/westi\";s:8:\"requires\";s:3:\"3.1\";s:6:\"tested\";s:3:\"5.2\";s:12:\"requires_php\";s:5:\"5.2.4\";s:13:\"compatibility\";a:0:{}s:6:\"rating\";d:76;s:7:\"ratings\";a:5:{i:5;i:21;i:4;i:2;i:3;i:5;i:2;i:3;i:1;i:6;}s:11:\"num_ratings\";i:37;s:15:\"support_threads\";i:1;s:24:\"support_threads_resolved\";i:1;s:10:\"downloaded\";i:252505;s:12:\"last_updated\";s:21:\"2019-04-24 3:35pm GMT\";s:5:\"added\";s:10:\"2009-06-19\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:52:\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-beta-tester/\";s:8:\"sections\";a:4:{s:11:\"description\";s:1355:\"<p>This plugin provides an easy way to get involved with Beta testing WordPress.</p>\n<p>Once installed it will enable you to upgrade your website to the latest Beta or Release candidate at the click of a button using the built in upgrader.</p>\n<p>By default once enabled it switches your website onto the point release development track.</p>\n<p>For the more adventurous there is the option to switch to the bleeding edge (trunk) of development.</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t forget to backup before you start!</p>\n<h3>Extra Settings</h3>\n<p>The <strong>Extra Settings</strong> tab may contain choices for testing features in trunk that require constants to be set. A checked feature will add a constant to the user&#8217;s <code>wp-config.php</code> file in the format as follows:</p>\n<pre><code>define( \'WP_BETA_TESTER_{$feature}\', true );\n</code></pre>\n<p>Unchecking the feature will remove the constant.</p>\n<p>This plugin resets the constants in <code>wp-config.php</code> on plugin activation and removes them on plugin deactivation. Use the filter <code>wp_beta_tester_config_path</code> to return a non-standard <code>wp-config.php</code> file path.</p>\n<p>If no settings are present there is no testing to be done that requires this feature.</p>\n<p>PRs are welcome on <a href=\"https://github.com/afragen/wordpress-beta-tester\" rel=\"nofollow\">GitHub</a>.</p>\n\";s:12:\"installation\";s:439:\"<ol>\n<li>Upload to your plugins folder, usually <code>wp-content/plugins/</code></li>\n<li>Activate the plugin on the plugin screen.</li>\n<li>Navigate to Tools &#8230; Beta Testing to configure the plugin.</li>\n<li>Under Mulitsite, navigate to Settings &#8230; Beta Testing to configure the plugin.</li>\n<li>Visit Dashboard &#8230; Upgrade (Or Tools &#8230; Upgrade in versions before 3.0) and update to the latest Beta Release.</li>\n</ol>\n\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:2306:\"<h4>2.0.4</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>add update version information to settings page text</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>a11y fixes for settings tabs</li>\n<li>update <code>wp-cli/wp-config-transformer</code></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>a11y fixes for checkbox, thanks @audrasjb</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>fix for incorrect last updated message</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>near complete re-write to use more OOPy practices</li>\n<li>put distinct process into separate classes</li>\n<li>allows for multiple settings tabs for addtional settings</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.6</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>remove extraneous code</li>\n<li>add GitHub Plugin URI header</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.5</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>fixed error message for downgrading version, thanks @andreas-andersson</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.4</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>don&#8217;t use $GLOBALS</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>updated a few strings and correct typos</li>\n<li>run through WPCS linter</li>\n<li>fixed translation strings to include HTML in context and properly escape with <code>wp_kses_post()</code></li>\n<li>fixed link to settings page under Multisite</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>change wording from blog to website</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.2.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Escape output</li>\n<li>Indicate that <em>Bleeding edge nightlies</em> are <em>trunk</em></li>\n<li>new screenshot</li>\n<li>code improvements from linter</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Remove anonymous function for PHP 5.2 compatibility.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>fixed PHP notice for PHP 7.1</li>\n<li>made URL scheme agnostic</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed to work properly under Multisite.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update tested up to version to 4.7.</li>\n<li>Fix the location of the settings screen in Multisite (moved under Settings in Network Admin).</li>\n<li>Minor text fixes.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update tested up to version to 4.5.</li>\n<li>Fix PHP7 deprecated constructor notice.</li>\n<li>Change text domain to match the plugin slug.</li>\n<li>Update WordPress.org links to use HTTPS.</li>\n<li>Remove outdated bundled translations in favor of language packs.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Update tested up to version to 4.2.</li>\n<li>Update screenshot.</li>\n<li>Fix a couple typos.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>See old-changelog.txt for previous changelog items</h4>\n\";s:11:\"screenshots\";s:611:\"<ol><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/wordpress-beta-tester/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=2074117\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/wordpress-beta-tester/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=2074117\" alt=\"This shows the main administration page for the plugin\"></a><p>This shows the main administration page for the plugin</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/wordpress-beta-tester/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=2074117\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/wordpress-beta-tester/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=2074117\" alt=\"This shows the Extra Settings page for the plugin\"></a><p>This shows the Extra Settings page for the plugin</p></li></ol>\";}s:13:\"download_link\";s:70:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.2.0.4.zip\";s:11:\"screenshots\";a:2:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:74:\"https://ps.w.org/wordpress-beta-tester/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=2074117\";s:7:\"caption\";s:54:\"This shows the main administration page for the plugin\";}i:2;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:74:\"https://ps.w.org/wordpress-beta-tester/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=2074117\";s:7:\"caption\";s:49:\"This shows the Extra Settings page for the plugin\";}}s:4:\"tags\";a:3:{s:8:\"advanced\";s:8:\"advanced\";s:4:\"beta\";s:4:\"beta\";s:7:\"testing\";s:7:\"testing\";}s:8:\"versions\";a:32:{s:3:\"0.5\";s:68:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.5.zip\";s:3:\"0.6\";s:68:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.6.zip\";s:3:\"0.7\";s:68:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.7.zip\";s:3:\"0.8\";s:68:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.8.zip\";s:4:\"0.81\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.81.zip\";s:4:\"0.90\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.90.zip\";s:4:\"0.91\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.91.zip\";s:4:\"0.92\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.92.zip\";s:4:\"0.93\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.93.zip\";s:4:\"0.94\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.94.zip\";s:4:\"0.95\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.95.zip\";s:4:\"0.96\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.96.zip\";s:4:\"0.97\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.97.zip\";s:4:\"0.98\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.98.zip\";s:4:\"0.99\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.0.99.zip\";s:3:\"1.0\";s:68:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-beta-tester.1.0.zip\";s:5:\"1.0.1\";s:70:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/wordpress-b